definition.value: A trisaccharide that is lactose in which the hydroxy group at the 3' position has been converted to the corresponding D-galactopyranosyl derivative.
An amino disaccharide that is beta-D-galactopyranose in which the hydroxy group at position 4 has been converted to the corresponding 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-beta-D-galactopyranoside.
A trisaccharide consisting of beta-L-fucopyranose, beta-D-galactopyranose and D-glucopyranose residues joined in sequence by (1->6) and (1->4) glycosidic bonds.
An alpha-L-Fucp-(1->6)-D-Glcp in which the carbon bearing the anomeric hydroxy group has beta configuration.
An amino disaccharide that is alpha-D-glactopyranose in which the hydroxy group at position 3 has been converted into the corresponding 2-acetamido-alpha-D-galactopyranoside.
A mannotetrose consisting of four alpha-D-mannopyranose residues linked by three (1->6) glycosidic bonds.
A disaccharide that is D-galactopyranose in which the hydroxy group at position 2 has been converted into the corresponding beta-D-glucopyranoside.
An aminotetrasaccharide that is beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-beta-D-Galp-(1->3)-GalpNAc in which the non-terminal galatopyranosyl group has been glycosylated at position 2 by an alpha-L-fucopyranosyl group.
A mannotriose that is alpha-D-mannopyranose in which the hydroxy groups at positions 2 and 4 have each been converted into the corresponding alpha-D-mannopyranoside.
